The paper discusses search engine research and user activities before, during, and after search, which are all related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also focuses on the role of social interactions in the search process, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper integrates models from previous work in sensemaking (cs.HCI) and information seeking behavior (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents a model for understanding social search, which could also be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social computing (cs.SOC).
